      "message": "I\u0027m not sure. I\u0027m willing to say yes, but the reason it was like this before:\n\nUnlike other mixed-vector-and-scalar intrinsics (eg, smoothstep), the GLSL reference pages for refract had eta being float, even for double-precision vectors (https://www.khronos.org/registry/OpenGL-Refpages/gl4/html/refract.xhtml).\n\nI think it was like that in the various spec docs, too. Looking at the most recent GLSL 4.6, it looks like it was just a spec bug that\u0027s been fixed. 4th bullet in section 1.1.2 of https://www.khronos.org/registry/OpenGL/specs/gl/GLSLangSpec.4.60.pdf.",
